<p itemprop="description">Data ethics and privacy involves understanding and applying ethical principles and privacy regulations in data collection, processing, and use, ensuring responsible and lawful handling of personal and sensitive data.</p>

<div class="proficiency-levels">
    <h2>Proficiency Levels</h2>

    <ol class="skill-levels">
        <li>
            <h3>Awareness</h3>
            <p>You can understand basic data protection principles and recognise when ethical considerations apply to data work.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Working</h3>
            <p>You can apply data protection regulations (like GDPR) in your work and identify potential ethical issues in data projects.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Practitioner</h3>
            <p>You can design data processes that comply with privacy regulations, conduct privacy impact assessments, and resolve complex ethical dilemmas in data use.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Expert</h3>
            <p>You can develop organisational data ethics frameworks, lead privacy strategy, and provide expert guidance on complex regulatory and ethical challenges.</p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>

